\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. D. aegyptius} (L.) Desv., {\i Jour. Bot. Appl.}{\b  3}:160 (1814). Erect annual 10-40 cm, sparsely hispid. Leaves oblong-elliptical, dentate to lyrate-pinnatisect with 2-5 pairs of lobes, or rarely 2-pinnatisect. Pedicels 3-5 mm in fruit. Sepals 3·5 4·5 mm; petals 6-10 mm, slightly emarginate. Silicula 6-10 mm; lower segment with 4-6 swellings at the base; upper segment ovoid, often tetragonal; beak 2·5-4 mm.{\i  S. Aegean region.} Cr Gr.
